    "discussion_id": "1742384282",
    "pr_number": 1603,
    "pr_file": "pyproject.toml",
    "created_at": "2024-09-03T16:50:26+00:00",
    "commented_code": "\"cached-property; python_version < '3.8'\",\n     \"tqdm > 4\",\n     \"jiter>=0.4.0, <1\",\n+    \"argcomplete >= 1.12.0\"",
    "repo_full_name": "openai/openai-python",
    "discussion_comments": [
      {
        "comment_id": "1742384282",
        "repo_full_name": "openai/openai-python",
        "pr_number": 1603,
        "pr_file": "pyproject.toml",
        "discussion_id": "1742384282",
        "commented_code": "@@ -17,6 +17,7 @@ dependencies = [\n     \"cached-property; python_version < '3.8'\",\n     \"tqdm > 4\",\n     \"jiter>=0.4.0, <1\",\n+    \"argcomplete >= 1.12.0\"",
        "comment_created_at": "2024-09-03T16:50:26+00:00",
        "comment_author": "RobertCraigie",
        "comment_body": "I'd like to avoid adding a new required dependency, can we add this as an optional dependency?\r\n\r\nI'm thinking something like this, thoughts?\r\n```\r\npip install openai[cli]\r\n```",
        "pr_file_module": null
      },
      {
        "comment_id": "1742740641",
        "repo_full_name": "openai/openai-python",
        "pr_number": 1603,
        "pr_file": "pyproject.toml",
        "discussion_id": "1742384282",
        "commented_code": "@@ -17,6 +17,7 @@ dependencies = [\n     \"cached-property; python_version < '3.8'\",\n     \"tqdm > 4\",\n     \"jiter>=0.4.0, <1\",\n+    \"argcomplete >= 1.12.0\"",
        "comment_created_at": "2024-09-03T21:53:59+00:00",
        "comment_author": "hoonman",
        "comment_body": "Thank you for the feedback! Our team discussed this and wanted to share our approach to add argcomplete as an optional dependency.\r\n\r\nTo avoid making argcomplete a required dependency, we plan to:\r\n\r\n1. Change `argcomplete` from a required to an optional dependency in `pyproject.toml`.\r\n2. Add a proxy file for `argcomplete` to handle optional imports.\r\n3. Update the `__init__.py` file in the extras directory to reflect these changes.\r\n4. Modify the README to instruct users to use the `[cli]` option to install `argcomplete`.\r\n\r\nPlease let us know if there are any additional changes we should consider. ",
        "pr_file_module": null
      },
      {
        "comment_id": "1742749755",
        "repo_full_name": "openai/openai-python",
        "pr_number": 1603,
        "pr_file": "pyproject.toml",
        "discussion_id": "1742384282",
        "commented_code": "@@ -17,6 +17,7 @@ dependencies = [\n     \"cached-property; python_version < '3.8'\",\n     \"tqdm > 4\",\n     \"jiter>=0.4.0, <1\",\n+    \"argcomplete >= 1.12.0\"",
        "comment_created_at": "2024-09-03T21:59:37+00:00",
        "comment_author": "RobertCraigie",
        "comment_body": "That sounds good to me! I don't think there's any other changes needed.\n\nFor what it's worth I don't think we need the complexity of a proxy here though as the dependency is only ever used in one place anyway we can just change that call site to `try ... except ImportError`",
        "pr_file_module": null
      },
      {
        "comment_id": "1742933120",
        "repo_full_name": "openai/openai-python",
        "pr_number": 1603,
        "pr_file": "pyproject.toml",
        "discussion_id": "1742384282",
        "commented_code": "@@ -17,6 +17,7 @@ dependencies = [\n     \"cached-property; python_version < '3.8'\",\n     \"tqdm > 4\",\n     \"jiter>=0.4.0, <1\",\n+    \"argcomplete >= 1.12.0\"",
        "comment_created_at": "2024-09-04T03:20:57+00:00",
        "comment_author": "hoonman",
        "comment_body": "We have included the changes for making `argcomplete` an optional dependency, the `try...except ImportError` to the `_cli.py`, as well as the `pip install openai[cli]` command in the README. Let me know if there's anything else that needs modification. Thank you!",
        "pr_file_module": null
      }
    ]
  },
